The paper deals with the problem of answering queries in a peer-to-peer data exchange system, which involves issues related to databases (cs.DB), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and security (cs.CR). The focus on semantic constraints and trust relationships also suggests a possible connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given the emphasis on data exchange and consistency, we believe that the first five categories are more likely to be relevant.
